cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Gemma4SwiftCore in your research or products, please cite it as below."
title: "Gemma4SwiftCore: Native Swift Inference for Google Gemma 4"
abstract: >-
  The first native Swift implementation of Google's Gemma 4 text decoder.
  Plugs into Apple's mlx-swift-lm as a sidecar model registration so any
  HuggingFace Gemma 4 repository can be loaded on iPhone, iPad, or Mac.
  Implements all five Gemma 4 architectural features that distinguish it
  from Gemma 3 (Per-Layer Embedding, KV sharing across the back half of
  the decoder, custom proportional RoPE, per-layer head dimensions, new
  chat protocol) and ships a chat-template bypass that produces token
  sequences identical to Python mlx-lm's apply_chat_template.
